========,1,preface.
Greenfield is a city in Dade County, Missouri.
The population was 1,371 at the 2010 census.
It is the county seat of Dade County.
========,2,History.
Greenfield was laid out in 1841, and named for the greenery of the original town site.
A post office called Greenfield has been in operation since 1850.
The Greenfield square is lined with buildings built in the 1880s out of bricks made in the Greenfield Brickyard.
The Greenfield Opera House Building, which opened in 1888, is known as the "Jewel of the Square" and is still used for the summer productions of the Dade County Community Theater.
It is listed on the National Register of Historic Places along with the Washington Hotel.
